made to the presentation of the performance audit <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">chapters</ENAMEX>.
Given the extensiveness of the proposed revisions, we plan to
issue a new version of <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">GAGAS</ENAMEX> that will incorporate existing
amendments. We expect this revision of the standards to supersede
the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1994</TIMEX> revision, including amendments <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">1 and 2</NUMEX>. Thereafter, we
intend to continue our policy of issuing amendments addressing
specific issues as needed. We anticipate this revision of the
standards, when finalized, will become effective for financial
audits of periods ending on or after <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">January 1, 2003</TIMEX>, and for
attestation engagements and performance audits beginning on or
after <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">January 1, 2003</TIMEX>.
